---
import ArticleLayout from '../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import { breadcrumbLd } from '../lib/jsonld';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
const path = '/contact/';
const crumbs = [{ name: 'Home', path: '/' }, { name: 'contact', path }];
---
<ArticleLayout
  title="Contact — Report a Bug or Suggest a Tool | PrivacyKit"
  description="Get in touch with PrivacyKit by email to report a bug, suggest a new browser tool, or flag a correction — plus a realistic response time to expect."
  path={path}
  h1="contact"
  crumbs={crumbs}
  jsonLd={[breadcrumbLd(crumbs)]}
>
  <h2>Email</h2>
  <p>The best way to reach PrivacyKit is email:</p>
  <p>
    <a href={`mailto:${SITE.contactEmail}`}>{SITE.contactEmail}</a>
  </p>

  <h2>What to write about</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>
      <strong>Bug reports</strong> — a tool gives a wrong result, breaks in your
      browser, or does something unexpected. Tell me which tool, which browser,
      and what you entered (leave out anything sensitive), and I can usually
      reproduce it.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Tool suggestions</strong> — a small, single-purpose utility you
      wish existed here. The ones that fit are the kind that can run client-side,
      without a server.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Corrections</strong> — a factual error in a guide, an out-of-date
      figure, or a formula that is off. Accuracy matters more than being right,
      so these are always welcome.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Privacy questions</strong> — anything about what a tool does with
      your data. The <a href="/privacy-policy/">privacy policy</a> covers the
      details, but ask if something is unclear.
    </li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Response time</h2>
  <p>
    PrivacyKit is run by one person around other work, so replies are not
    instant. Expect a few days, sometimes a little longer during busy stretches.
    Every genuine message gets read; obvious spam and SEO pitches do not get a
    reply.
  </p>
  <p>
    There is no contact form here on purpose — a form would need a backend
    collecting your details, which runs against the point of the site. Plain
    email keeps it uncomplicated and leaves you in control of what you share.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
